### Company or project name
ClickHouse Inc.
### Question
The [docs](https://clickhouse.com/docs/sql-reference/statements/select/limit) for `LIMIT` say: `LIMIT m - if 0 < m < 1, then the first m * 100% of rows are returned.`
However, if I run
```sql
CREATE TABLE users (uid Int16, name String, age Int16) ENGINE=Memory;
INSERT INTO users VALUES (1231, 'John', 33);
INSERT INTO users VALUES (6666, 'Ksenia', 48);
INSERT INTO users VALUES (8888, 'Alice', 50);
SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 0.5;
```
I get an error `LIMIT numeric constant expression is not representable as UInt64 or Int64. (INVALID_LIMIT_EXPRESSION)`.
(Side note, this syntax would be more intuitive: `SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 50%`.)
